This is yummy as a bowl. Rice, hummus, parsley, some sort of sauce, pickled onion, cucumber, etc, etc ,etc

A lime mayo cilantro sauce would be yummy, etc.

INGREDIENTS
1 onion
2 teaspoons minced garlic
1/2 carrot
2 cups cooked chickpeas
1/8 cup fresh parsley
1/2 teaspoon ground cumin
1/2 teaspoon ground coriander
1/2 teaspoon ground black pepper
1/2 teaspoon paprika
1/2 teaspoon coarse sea salt
1/8 teaspoon cayenne pepper
1/2 cup chickpea flour, (or substitute flour of your choice)
1/2 cup extra virgin olive oil
1/2 large cucumber
tahini sauce
HOW TO PREPARE
1.	Coarsely chop the onions. Set aside.
2.	Grate the carrot (either by hand or using the grating attachment of your food processor). Place grated carrot in a large bowl.
3.	With the s-blade in place, place parsley in a food processor and pulse until well chopped. Add to carrots in bowl.
4.	In batches, pulse the chickpeas and onions to create a paste-like consistency. Add to bowl with carrots and parsley.
5.	In a separate bowl add garlic, cumin, coriander, black pepper, paprika, sea salt and cayenne with the chickpea flour and combine well. Add this mixture to the bowl with the chickpeas and veggies. Using clean hands, combine well.
6.	Make into small patties (1 T. each).
7.	In a large pan, heat olive oil over medium high heat. In small batches, fry falafel patties for 1-2 minutes on each side, transferring to a towel lined plate to drain. Quarter and slice cucumbers. Serve falafel warm with sliced cucumbers and tahini sauce.
